<HEADLINE>
<P>
MIXED MEDIA; 
</P>
<P>
** 1/2 "THE RISE OF NENEH CHERRY" NENEH CHERRY BMG VIDEO VIDEOCASSETTE 
($16.98): A PERIODIC SURVEY OF POP-RELATED LASER DISCS, BOOKS AND 
VIDEOCASSETTES. RATED ON A SCALE OF ONE (POOR) TO FIVE STARS (A CLASSIC.) 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DENNIS HUNT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
This is everything you ever wanted to know about Cherry, who emerged last year 
as a promising soul singer and rapper -- plus a whole lot you didn't want to 
know. 
</P>
<P>
While a welcome change from simple clip compilations that offer no extras, this 
65-minute video verges on information overload -- trivial information. Do you 
really want to see her being made up for photo sessions or exchanging inanities 
with adoring fans during radio station chats? The behind-the scenes footage, 
while occassionally amusing, is self-serving. Surprisingly, the performance 
segments, featuring songs like her hit "Buffalo Stance" and "Inner City Mama," 
aren't the main focus. That may have been a wise decision, because Cherry seems 
to have limited talent. DENNIS HUNT 
</P>
