<HEADLINE>
<P>
ANC LEADER TAMBO LEAVES SWEDISH CLINIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
STOCKHOLM 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
South African black leader Oliver Tambo has left Sweden after nearly four 
months of medical treatment for a stroke, the Swedish news agency TT said 
Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Tambo, 72, president of the African National Congress, flew to London last week 
and was expected to travel to South Africa soon, the agency said. 
</P>
