<HEADLINE>
<P>
HANDLING OF STUDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
We have been following the stories about Robert Davis, the John H. Francis 
Polytechnic High School student recently arrested for living above the school's 
auditorium. 
</P>
<P>
It would seem more appropriate for Principal Virginia Holt to have referred him 
to a school counselor or social worker for housing assistance. 
</P>
<P>
The city attorney's time would be better spent appealing decisions that return 
students who have assaulted teachers to the classroom. 
</P>
<P>
This procedural mentality is the foundation of the educational crisis. It 
stifles creativity and initiative to maintain custodial integrity. We hope the 
mishandling of the situation has a greater impact on Holt's career than on that 
of Davis. 
</P>
<P>
WILLIAM PIRONE 
</P>
<P>
ANN LARSEN 
</P>
<P>
Sherman Oaks 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA042990-0050 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 211183 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
April 29, 1990, Sunday, Ventura County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Metro; Part B; Page 6; Column 1 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
210 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
GET RID OF GALLEGLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rep. Elton Gallegly (R-Simi Valley) has been talking out of both sides of his 
mouth for years: 
</P>
<P>
1. He claims to be an environmentalist, yet he co-sponsored a bill to open the 
Arctic National Wildlife Refuge to oil and gas exploration and supports 
increased offshore drilling off the California coastline. 
</P>
<P>
2. He claims to be a friend to senior citizens, yet he voted to lower funding 
for the Older Americans Act. 
</P>
<P>
3. He claims his only opposition to abortion is that he opposes paying for the 
procedure with federal funds, yet he supported a constitutional ban on 
abortion. 
</P>
<P>
4. He claims to be a staunch supporter of law and order, yet he voted against a 
raise in overtime pay for federal law enforcement officials. 
</P>
<P>
And now, through recently released FBI documents, we find out that he lied 
about the conduct of FBI agents, manipulated the FBI into conducting an 
unnecessary investigation and lied several times to the public at large -- all 
to benefit his campaign for reelection. 
</P>
<P>
How long will the 21st District be fooled by this paranoid liar wearing the 
"Teflon suit"? If they think he is qualified to be our representative in 
Washington, well, I have some prime real estate for sale in the Florida 
swamplands. 
</P>
<P>
LINDA JORDAN-O'CONNOR 
</P>
<P>
Simi Valley 
</P>
</TEXT>
