<HEADLINE>
<P>
SHERIFF'S RACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A community group in Fallbrook held a meeting with all the candidates for 
sheriff a week ago, which was most enlightening. I would hope that more groups 
do the same, because there doesn't appear to be much in the press about this 
very important race. 
</P>
<P>
One observation made was a statement by one of the candidates, a Mr. (Jack) 
Drown. He said he has worked for no one else but the Sheriff's Department in 
his entire adult life -- over 20 years providing us, the citizens of this 
county, with the best law enforcement possible, claiming that no other 
candidate matches his experience and skills. 
</P>
<P>
Well, all I have to say is that, if the current state of the Sheriff's 
Department is due to Mr. Drown's best efforts and vast experience and 
leadership, I suggest he do us all a favor and step aside and allow change to 
take place. It's apparent that he and Sheriff John Duffy haven't got it right 
in 20 years. We can't afford another 20. 
</P>
<P>
DAMON THORNBURG 
