<HEADLINE>
<P>
VACCINATION PRICES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I am responding to a recent letter from a woman who felt that more children 
would receive their vaccinations if the prices charged by private physicians 
were more in line with what they used to be. 
</P>
<P>
When I started pediatric practice in Orange County about 17 years ago, vaccines 
were supplied free by the county health department to physicians who agreed not 
to charge for them. 
</P>
<P>
Many things economic have changed over time. 
</P>
<P>
Today there is only one source for measles-mumps-rubella vaccine. The price per 
dose that I must pay is $24.11. Please note that this price includes $4.44 
federal excise tax to fund the federal vaccine injury program. The $24.11 cost 
does not include the cost of a syringe or other office overhead. 
</P>
<P>
DR. MARTIN J. ROSENFELD 
</P>
<P>
Santa Ana 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
