<HEADLINE>
<P>
CSUN CLINCHES SOFTBALL TITLE WITH SWEEP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Cal State Northridge softball team secured its ninth consecutive California 
Collegiate Athletic Assn. title Saturday by sweeping a doubleheader from UC 
Riverside at Lady Matador Field. 
</P>
<P>
Overall, Northridge pounded out 21 hits -- including four doubles -- and 
pitchers Debbie Dickmann and De Dow held Riverside to 10 singles as the Lady 
Matadors claimed their eighth undisputed conference championship in the past 
nine years with 3-1 and 7-0 wins. 
</P>
<P>
The Lady Matadors have won 11 of their past 12 games and 10 conference games in 
a row. 
</P>
<P>
Northridge, which has four conference games left, holds a four-game lead over 
Cal State Bakersfield, which has concluded conference play. Third-place Cal 
Poly San Luis Obispo is five games behind heading into a doubleheader today at 
CSUN. 
</P>
<P>
In the first game, Dickmann surrendered six hits and struck out six to improve 
to 20-7, and Erin McGuire went two for three with two runs batted in. 
</P>
<P>
Dow (8-5) scattered four singles in the second game to record her fifth shutout 
of the season, and Lisa Erickson went three for three with an RBI and two runs 
for the Lady Matadors (40-18 overall, 15-1 in conference play). 
</P>
<P>
UC Riverside threatened briefly in the fourth inning of the opening game, 
trimming an early CSUN lead to 2-1. But Erickson scored on McGuire's single in 
the home half of the inning to provide the final margin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
