<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOTOCROSS DUEL BETWEEN BREWER, GRAY INTENSIFIES AT VENTURA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PAUL OLSON, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Josh Brewer of Oak View and Mike Gray of Ventura each won two races in the 
125cc beginner class Saturday night at Ventura Raceway to keep their motocross 
season points battle close. 
</P>
<P>
Brewer leads the division with 126 points and Gray has 123. 
</P>
<P>
But while most of the points leaders in the other divisions failed to pick up 
victories Saturday, there was an abundance of double winners. 
</P>
<P>
Mark Stuen of Simi Valley and Kyle Lewis of Simi Valley were double winners in 
the 125cc junior and pro divisions, respectively. 
</P>
<P>
Other two-time winners included Gary Baker of Westlake Village and Mark Fildes 
of Ventura in the 250cc beginner division; Kenny Millsaps of Lompoc in the 
veteran pro division; Don Kadler of Santa Barbara in the 500cc beginner 
division; Frankie Politelli of Canyon Country in the quad 250cc division; and 
Lewis again in the 250cc pro division. 
</P>
<P>
Ron Carter of Culver City outclassed the field to win the 12-lap Class 10 
buggies main event. Randy Rinehart of Palmdale finished second and Richard 
Litton of Culver City took third. 
</P>
<P>
Rinehart and Carter each won a heat race in the Class 10 buggies. Rinehart had 
the fast lap for the class at 19.633 seconds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
