<HEADLINE>
<P>
GRAND OPENINGS: SINGLE-FAMILY PROJECTS OPEN IN LAGUNA NIGUEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Chateau Collection and the Terrace Collection, two single-family 
developments by the Frost Group totaling 120 houses, open today across from 
Crown Valley Park in Laguna Niguel. 
</P>
<P>
Featuring contemporary Mediterranean design by Bassenian/Lagoni of Newport 
Beach, the developments are part of the planned community of Chatelaine 
Estates. Exteriors have stucco, decorative stone or red brick, with barrel-tile 
or concrete-tile roofs. 
</P>
<P>
The Terrace Collection, with a total of 65 three- and four-bedroom houses, 
opens with 10 houses ranging in size from 2,124 to 2,488 square feet, priced 
from $324,900 to $389,900. 
</P>
<P>
The first phase of the Chateau Collection has 10 four- and five-bedroom houses, 
with 2,784 to 3,369 square feet, priced from $399,900 to $479,900. Chateau 
Collection houses have three-car garages, with two-car garages offered in the 
Terrace Collection. 
</P>
<P>
The monthly association dues are about $100, and July move-ins are planned for 
both projects. Carole Eichen Interiors decorated the Terrace Collection model 
homes, with Saddleback Interiors handling decoration of the Chateau models. 
Models are open from 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. daily at Central Park Drive, just off 
Crown Valley Parkway, reached from the southbound Crown Valley Parkway exit of 
the San Diego (5) Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Next to Parkland 
</P>
<P>
Windchime, a 283-unit single-family development by Russell/Packard, opens today 
in the master-planned Southridge community in Fontana. 
</P>
<P>
The 15 houses in the first phase are offered in four one- and two-story plans 
with three or four bedrooms and 1,245 to 1,854 square feet. Prices range from 
$132,990 to $162,990, and first-phase move-ins are scheduled for August. 
</P>
<P>
Sixteen elevations are available and standard features include window 
coverings, front-yard landscaping with sprinklers and side and rear fencing. 
</P>
<P>
Southridge is adjacent to Jurupa Hills Regional Park, with 325 acres of 
parklands and 400 acres of designated open space. Southridge itself has 
recreational facilities, including a swimming pool a 1,000-seat performing-arts 
center and a clubhouse. 
</P>
<P>
Four furnished models are open daily 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. at 16121 Trailwinds 
Drive, reached from the southbound Citrus Avenue exit of the San Bernardino 
(10) Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Golf Course Condos 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles-area home buyers who want a Palm Springs-style golf course 
condominium without the long drive to the Coachella Valley can find it at 
Upland Hills Trophy Series, opening today in Upland. 
</P>
<P>
The 136-unit gate-guarded project by Breslow Development Corp., a unit of 
Goldrich &amp; Kest Industries, opens with 28 two- and three-bedroom units in 
one-story plans ranging from 1,632 to 2,000 square feet. 
</P>
<P>
The 226-acre development includes an 18-hole golf course designed by David 
Rainville, a pro shop, tennis courts, swimming pools, spas and a clubhouse. 
</P>
<P>
Prices range from $214,000 to $255,000 and the units feature two-car garages 
with golf-cart storage areas, front landscaping, fencing, spa tubs in the 
master bathrooms and walk-in closets or regular closets with mirrored doors. 
</P>
<P>
The monthly association fee is $155; move-ins are scheduled to begin in August 
and September. Four furnished models are open from 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. at 1310 
Upland Hills Drive North, reached from the northbound Euclid Avenue exit of the 
San Bernardino (10) Freeway, east on 16th Street to Upland Hills Drive North. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Near Del Mar Track 
</P>
<P>
Del Mar Legends, 21 two-bedroom townhouses by Cirrus Development Group, La 
Jolla, opens today in Solana Beach, within walking distance of the Del Mar Race 
Track. 
</P>
<P>
Eight units have been sold; the 13 remaining units have 1,853 to 1,897 square 
feet in two two-story floor plans, priced from $300,000 to $320,000. 
</P>
<P>
Designed by the Pacific Group, a Del Mar-based architectural firm, the project 
features Cape Cod-influenced architecture, with gray wood siding, white trim, 
high-pitched roofs and clerestory windows. 
</P>
<P>
Both the Citation and Sea Bisquit plans feature two-car attached garages with 
automatic door openers and direct access to the units, wood-burning fireplaces, 
walk-in closets, ceramic-tiled entries, central vacuum cleaner systems and 
laundry rooms. 
</P>
<P>
Move-ins are scheduled for June. The monthly association fee is $181. A model 
decorated by Homes by Nancy Adams is open 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. daily at Del Mar 
Downs Road and Peppertree Lane, reached from the westbound Via de la Valle exit 
of the San Diego (5) Freeway. 
</P>
</TEXT>
