<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEACE DIVIDEND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Congress is making a big issue of the "peace dividend." 
</P>
<P>
However, there is a parallel between Shakespeare ("Merchant of Venice") whose 
character, Portia said: "Take ye your pound of flesh but take ye not one drop 
of blood" and congressmen who say: "Cut billions from the defense budget but 
cut not one dollar from my district." Until we can overcome this provincialism, 
there will not be a meaningful peace dividend. 
</P>
<P>
GARY A. ROBB 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
