AFTERSHOCKS CAUSE PROPERTY DAMAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and Wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Inspectors found toppled chimneys and minor structural cracks Saturday in an 
area on the east side of San Francisco Bay rocked by two moderate earthquakes. 
</P>
<P>
The jolts, which struck along the southern end of the small Concord fault 
Friday night, measured 4.6 and 4.3 and were followed by several smaller 
temblors, according to the U.S. Geological Survey. USGS geologist Rick Lester 
said the quakes were considered aftershocks from a similar jolt April 6, which 
has been followed by a swarm of about 300 tiny temblors. "This could go on for 
a couple of weeks or stop abruptly," said Lester, adding that a similar 
sequence in the area in 1970 lasted for several months. 
</P>
