<HEADLINE>
<P>
FBI ARRESTS COUPLE WHO ALLEGEDLY FLED SEPARATE DRUG TRIALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From a Times Staff Writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BUENA PARK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FBI agents Saturday arrested a man charged in Dallas with fleeing from a 
cocaine indictment. 
</P>
<P>
Agents said they arrested Kevin Pressley Johnson, 23, of Baltimore without 
incident after he was seen driving near La Palma and Knott avenues. 
</P>
<P>
Johnson was indicted last July in Dallas for possessing cocaine for delivery, 
agents said. A federal warrant was issued after it appeared that he had fled 
the state. 
</P>
<P>
Agents also arrested Sarah Dyer, 30, of Buena Park, Johnson's companion. 
</P>
<P>
She is wanted on a Los Angeles County warrant for failure to appear in court on 
a drug charge and was turned over to Buena Park police, agents said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
