<HEADLINE>
<P>
CURRENTS: A GUIDE TO THE BEST OF SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA; 
</P>
<P>
AT HOME; 
</P>
<P>
MADAME BUTTERFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DENISE HAMILTON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
IN THE MARKET for a Giant Death's Head roach? A Horned Rhinoceros beetle? Maybe 
a lavender grasshopper? Cathy Endfield can help. 
</P>
<P>
In film and video circles, she's known as the butterfly lady. Endfield is a 
specialist in insect art. Her Sherman Oaks home is crammed with insects -- 
thousands of them, stashed in drawers, mounted and hoarded in bags. Endfield 
rents her bugs to film studios, special-effects shops, photographers and anyone 
else with such a hankering. 
</P>
<P>
Recently Endfield supplied insects for "Arachnophobia," an Amblin-Hollywood 
Pictures production. But creating art pieces by incorporating these creatures 
into collages and assemblages is her true avocation. "I'm into insect art," the 
butterfly lady says. 
</P>
<P>
 For further information, telephone Cathy Endfield; (818) 783-4357. DENISE 
HAMILTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, COLOR, Butterflies Claudia Kunin 
