<P>
CURRENTS: A GUIDE TO THE BEST OF SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA; 
</P>
<P>
FAVORITES; 
</P>
<P>
SAFE AND STORED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DOLORES A. LONG 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STILL STORING THOSE oil paintings in the attic? The vintage Bordeaux in the 
kitchen cabinet? The Los Angeles Fine Arts &amp; Wine Storage Co. has a better 
idea. Designed to store anything from Picassos to port in temperature- and 
humidity-controlled compartments, this high-tech storage facility just opened 
in West Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
"It's a way to offer first-class protection for any collectible," says Bo 
Zarnegin, whose own family's art collections inspired the warehouse idea. 
</P>
<P>
The art compartments are spacious enough to hold anything from paintings to 
statues and large-scale 3-D pieces. In addition to the large walk-in 
compartments, which can expand even beyond 20 feet square, there's a 
comfortable art-viewing and wine-tasting room where collectors and enophiles 
can trade, sell or sample one anothers' wares. The Los Angeles Fine Arts &amp; 
Wine Storage Co. also features around-the-clock electronic security service and 
personal-access key cards. 
</P>
<P>
Collectors of other types of valuables can lease compartments to keep furs, 
rugs, film, tapes and legal files safe from theft and the elements. 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles Fine Arts &amp; Wine Storage Co., 2290 Centinela Ave., Los Angeles; 
(213) 447-7700. DOLORES A. LONG 
</P>
</TEXT>
